title: $A down after RBA minutes released
text:
Tue, Jul 21, 2015, 12:31 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 29 mins $A down after RBA minutes released AAP â€“ 8 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is lower after the Reserve Bank said developments in Greece and China would influence future interest rate decisions. 
At 1200 AEST on Tuesday, the currency was trading at 73.65 US cents, down from 73.90 cents on Monday. 
In the minutes of the RBA's July meeting, released on Tuesday, the central bank said it would closely monitor recent volatility in Chinese equity markets, potential spillovers from the Greek debt crisis, and subdued domestic business investment in the months ahead. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 73.65 US cents, from 73.90 cents on Monday 
* 91.58 Japanese yen, from 91.73 yen 
* 68.05 euro cents, from 68.17 euro cents 
* 111.70 New Zealand cents, from 112.08 NZ cents 
* 47.34 British pence, from 47.33 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.981%, from 1.964%, on Monday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 3.023%, from 2.995% 
* Sept 2015 10-year bond futures contract, at 97.015 (yield 2.985 pct), down from 97.040 (2.960 pct) 
* Sept 2015 3-year bond futures contract, at 97.940 (2.060 pct), down from 97.970 (2.030 per cent) 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
